					<tr>
                    <td width="3%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                    <td width="70%"><p>NEBOSH International Construction Certificate course is for:</p>
                      <p>Professionals across the world who work in construction, civil engineering, infrastructure, utilities and more, and who need the right level of skills and knowledge in identifying and controlling common construction hazards to fulfill their <a href="http://nist.co.in/index.php" target="_blank">health and safety responsibilities</a>.</p><p>
					  This course provides guidance to the professionals a comprehensive awareness on hazards and risks in their workplace and to progress the construction coordination in safe manner with systematic procedures.</p></td>
                    <td width="4%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>				  
					<tr>
                    <td width="3%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                    <td width="70%"><p>Benefits:</p>
                      <p>The Risks in a construction industry is more from low level to life threatening. The need of a safety officer having an excellent knowledge and talent in handling construction threats is a benefit for an industry and for the workers who work in that industry. This NEBOSH International Construction course makes those experts to be more proficiency at their work.</p><p>
					  The International Construction Certificate course is the foundation for the ultimate goal for any HSE professionals that are pursuing <a href="NEBOSH_International_Diploma.php" target="_self">International Diploma in NEBOSH</a>.</p><p>
					  It enhances recognition and financial benefits for existing HSE professionals.</p><p>
					  Certificate in Construction Health and Safety know how to help employers avoid prosecution, litigation, absence costs and loss of reputation.</p><p>
					  <a href="http://www.nebosh.org.uk/Qualifications/Certificate/default.asp?cref=94&ct=2" target="_blank">Certification in NEBOSH</a> meets the academic requirements for Technician Membership (Tech IOSH) of <a href="http://www.iosh.co.uk/default.aspx" target="_blank">Institution of Occupational Safety and Health</a> (IOSH) and Associate <a href="Membership.php" target="_self">membership</a> (AIIRSM) of the <a href="http://www.iirsm.org/" target="_blank">International Institute of Risk &amp; Safety Management</a> (IIRSM).</p></td>
                    <td width="4%"  valign="top" >&nbsp;</td>
                  </tr>	
