					<h3>Course Syllabus</h3>
								
						<p>Unit IGC 1: Management of International Health &amp; Safety<br /> 	<br /> 
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Foundations in Health and safety<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Health and Safety management policy<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Health and safety management system-organizing<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Health and safety management system-planning<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Health and safety management system-measuring, audit and review<br /><br />
							
							Unit ICC1: Managing and controlling hazards in international construction activities <br />	 <br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Construction management<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Construction site hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Manual and mechanical handling hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Electrical Hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fire hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chemical and biological health hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Physical, psychological health, hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Working at heights-hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Excavation work and confined spaces hazards and control<br />
							&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Demolition - Hazards and control<br /><br />
							
							Unit ICC2: International construction health and safety practical application 	 <br /><br />
							To carry out unaided safety inspection of a construction workplace, identifying more common hazards, deciding whether they are adequately controlled, suggesting appropriate cost effective remedial action, complete a report management regarding the inspections with recommendation. 	 
							<br /><br />
						</p>
					</li>
