						<h3>Training Methodology</h3>
						<span><img src="images/plus.png" alt="plus" height="20"></span>
						<p><a href="http://www.nistelearning.com/" target="_blank">E-Learning</a> approach is well systematized; it lets you to ease and stretches your concentration to learn so that you will gain excellent knowledge over the subject. </p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<h3>Assessment Method</h3>
						<span><img src="images/plus.png" alt="plus" height="20"></span>
						<p>NEBOSH International Construction certification assessment consists of two examinations (Unit I &amp; Unit II) & a practical construction health and safety practical application.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<h3>Exemption</h3>
						<span><img src="images/plus.png" alt="plus" height="20"></span>
						<p><a href="nebosh.php" target="_self">International General Certificate</a> (IGC1) is the core unit for all of the NEBOSH International Health and Safety Certificates, so to advance a NEBOSH Certificate you need to study IGC1 along with the applicable specialist unit and practical assessment. If you have been awarded a NEBOSH International Certification the last 5 years and wish to take another, you will be exempt from IGC1 and can simply add the specialist unit (ICC1) and practical assessment (ICC2) to achieve the new award.</p>
